body:
Another problem is that this was merged without checking test results.
One problem is that  the updated php docker images haven't been uploaded to dockerhub and so the PHP tests don't even start running:

https://source.cloud.google.com/results/invocations/095686f9-dadd-4cf5-8327-1138cf43ea33/targets/github%2Fgrpc%2Faggregate_tests/tests

```
+ DOCKER_IMAGE_NAME=php_jessie_x64_80146e3731996cce2cdd054cab60b0ead537a266
+ '[' grpctesting '!=' '' ']'
+ DOCKER_IMAGE_NAME=grpctesting/php_jessie_x64_80146e3731996cce2cdd054cab60b0ead537a266
+ docker pull grpctesting/php_jessie_x64_80146e3731996cce2cdd054cab60b0ead537a266
Using default tag: latest
Error response from daemon: pull access denied for grpctesting/php_jessie_x64_80146e3731996cce2cdd054cab60b0ead537a266, repository does not exist or may require 'docker login'
Traceback (most recent call last):
  File "tools/run_tests/run_tests.py", line 1575, in <module>
    env=env)
  File "/usr/lib/python2.7/subprocess.py", line 540, in check_call
    raise CalledProcessError(retcode, cmd)
subprocess.CalledProcessError: Command 'tools/run_tests/dockerize/build_docker_and_run_tests.sh' returned non-zero exit status 1
``` 

see https://github.com/grpc/grpc/blob/master/tools/dockerfile/push_testing_images.sh
Oh that's what the error is about. I spent some time today looking into this error without understanding it. Sorry about that.
